I""<blockquote>
  <p>Inspired by the ‘mental imagery’, emotion and the study and treatment of bipolar disorder, <em>Pictures of You</em> presents the intriguing meeting of two friends after many years apart. Full of unexpected lightness, warmth and love, the play explores the challenge of recalling the past and picturing the future… ~Menagerie</p>
</blockquote>

<p>In <a href="http://www.menagerie.uk.com/">Menagerie</a>’s <em>What’s Up Doc?</em> series playwrights were paired with academic collaborators. For this play written by <a href="https://www.ice.cam.ac.uk/about-us/staff-profiles/tutor/craig-baxter">Craig Baxter</a> the collaborator was <a href="http://www.neuroscience.cam.ac.uk/directory/profile.php?martidisi">Dr Martina Di Simplicio</a> from the MRC Cognition and Brain Sciences Unit, Cambridge.</p>

